# Canon CODEOWNERS
#
# Data owners defined here receive a PR review request whenever someone edits
# a domain folder. GitHub also uses this file to enforce the review gate on merge.
#
# HOW TO ADD DOMAIN OWNERS:
#   1. Uncomment the /domains/<slug>/ line below (or add a new one).
#   2. Replace @handle with real GitHub usernames.
#   3. The same handles should appear in scan-config.yaml → domains[].owners
#      so they also get @mentioned on drift issues from the scheduled scan.
#   4. Open a PR with both changes together so ownership is consistent.
#
# Format: <path pattern> <github-username> [<github-username> ...]
# See: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# Shared conventions
/shared/ @Jonvoge

# Connectors and serving
/connectors/ @Jonvoge
/serving/ @Jonvoge

# Automation
/.github/workflows/ @Jonvoge

# Schemas
